name: 7 - Verify Transaction Fee API call with different types of DISCOVER with PAYSAFE7861 processor

testSteps.description: Example #1: {NICN=DiscoverCore, Amount=108.00, Region=Chargeable state, Processor=Paysafe7861, HttpStatusCode=201, TransactionFee=Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage, Sid=NotNull, Message=ok}

children.description:
When I call Transaction Fee API with the following data
| Merchant | NICN | Amount | Region | Processor |
| Coastline | DiscoverCore | 108.00 | Chargeable state | Paysafe7861 |

Load transaction fee api request:       | Merchant  | NICN         | Amount | Region           | Processor   |
      | Coastline | DiscoverCore | 108.00 | Chargeable state | Paysafe7861 |
Execute transaction fee api request

Then Verify the response is as follows
| HttpStatusCode | TransactionFee | Fee | Sid | Message |
| 201 | Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage | <Fee> | NotNull | ok |

Load expected api response:       | HttpStatusCode | TransactionFee                                                 | Fee   | Sid     | Message |
      | 201            | Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage | <Fee> | NotNull | ok      |
Verify response
